history.content: Since EECS 126 and 127 are recommended as prerequisites for CS 189, I would personally recommend switching out 189 for 170 and taking 126. While 170, 126, and 127 (or really any three technicals) might be too difficult or time consuming, if you can handle it, that's what I would recommend.

children.subject: He mentioned it's fine to do 127 with 189.

Since you've already taken Stat 134, EE 126 will be a bit redundant and so I'd suggest taking 170 instead.

I strongly suggest you don't do those three in one semester. Based on what Sahai has repeatedly mentioned here you should take 127 before 189

history.content:
I have to make a choice between EECS 126 and CS 170 next semester. Other EECS classes I am taking will be CS189, EECS 127 so I hope to choose the one with less workload&difficulty between the two. I heard that 170 is hard but it seems that many math geniuses are taking 126 so the grade will be tough.

  1. Any suggestions in making the decision?

  2. Will 127 still be helpful if taken along with 189 in same semester?

Classes Taken: 61ABC 70 Stat134 Math 53 EE16AB last year, got A and A+s but had never been to lecture more than twice in any of them.
history.subject: EECS 126 or CS 170
